<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Surftrip Around Indonesia & Sri Lanka</title>

  <!-- External CSS Files with Rails Asset Pipeline -->
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag 'application', media: 'all' %>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag 'scrolling-wrapper', media: 'all' %>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag 'img' %>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag 'alert' %>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag 'footer' %>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag 'video' %>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag 'navbar' %>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag 'framevintage' %>
  <%# <%= stylesheet_link_tag 'play-pause-button' %>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag 'avatar', media: 'all' %>

  <!-- Optionally include Javascript -->
  <%= javascript_include_tag 'application', 'data-turbolinks-track': 'reload' %>

</head>

<body>
  <!-- Header Section with Banner and Navigation -->
  <header>
    <div class="banner">
      <!-- Avatar placed inside the .banner -->
      <div class="avatar-container" onclick="showPresentation()">
          <%= image_tag "medewi/me-sunrise.jpg",
            class: "avatar-large", alt: "avatar-large" %>
        </div>

      <!-- Modal for presentation -->
      <div id="presentation-modal" class="presentation-modal">
        <div class="modal-content">
          <h2>About Me</h2>
          <p>Hi, I’m Tifène!</p>
          <p>After finishing my Master’s degree in Human Resources and spending a year working at an international bank, I realized I needed a change. I wanted to reconnect with what truly makes me happy—the ocean. So, I packed my bags and spent 10 amazing months surfing in Indonesia (mostly) and Sri Lanka.</p>
          <p>Along the way, I decided to challenge myself in a new way and started learning how to code with Le Wagon. It’s been such an incredible journey! This site is personal and heartfelt, with all photos taken by me, except for the two on the welcome page. It's a fun and genuine journey, not professional content. I hope you enjoy exploring it as much as I did creating it!</p>
          <button onclick="document.getElementById('presentation-modal').style.display = 'none';">Close</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Video background for the banner -->
      <video autoplay muted loop class="banner-video">
        <source src="<%= asset_path('drone.mp4') %>" type="video/mp4">
        Your browser does not support the video tag.
      </video>

      <!-- Banner Text -->
      <div class="banner-text">
        <h1>𐌔𐌵𐌓𐌅 𐌕𐌓𐌉𐌐 𐌀𐌓Ꝋ𐌵𐌍𐌃 𐌉𐌍𐌃Ꝋ𐌍𐌄𐌔𐌉𐌀 & 𐌔R𐌉 𐌋𐌀𐌍𐌊𐌀</h1>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Navigation menu -->
    <nav>
      <!-- Hamburger icon -->
      <div class="hamburger" onclick="toggleMenu()">
        <div></div>
        <div></div>
        <div></div>
      </div>

      <!-- Navigation links -->
      <ul>
        <li><%= link_to 'Lombok', lombok_path %></li>
        <li><%= link_to 'Medewi', medewi_path %></li>
        <li><%= link_to 'Bukit Bali', bukit_bali_path %></li>
        <li><%= link_to 'Sumbawa', sumbawa_path %></li>
        <li><%= link_to 'Arugam Bay', arugam_bay_path %></li>
      </ul>
   </nav>

    <script>
      function toggleMenu() {
        const nav = document.querySelector('nav');
        const hamburger = document.querySelector('.hamburger');
        nav.classList.toggle('active');
        hamburger.classList.toggle('active');
      }
    </script>
</header>

  <!-- Main Content Section -->
  <main class="vintage-frame">
    <section>
      <!-- Flash Alert -->
      <div class="flash flash-warning alert alert-dismissible fade show" role="alert">
        <div class="flash-text">
          <p>This site is my little corner to learn and grow in coding. You can click on the avatar of me for more information.</p>
        </div>
        <a data-bs-dismiss="alert" aria-label="Close">
          <i class="fas fa-times"></i>
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- Indonesia Section -->
      <h2>Indonesia</h2>
      <img src="https://www.stokedfortravel.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/best-bali-surf-spots-uluwatu-padang-keramas-canggu-medewi-1920x960.jpg"
           width="500" height="250" alt="Indonesia Surf Spot">
      <p>A goofy paradise.</p>
      <p>With plenty of choices of islands and surf spots, you'll always find something that'll please you, from
        epic surf breaks that might just make you question your life choices, to waterfalls that are
        Instagram-worthy and rice paddies so green they'll make your eyes do a double-take.</p>
      <p>Plus, the Indonesian people are some of the friendliest you'll ever meet, always ready to share a smile, a story, or an
        incredible local dish. It’s a place where the waves are as warm as the welcome.</p>

      <!-- Sri Lanka Section -->
      <h2>Sri Lanka</h2>
      <img src="https://assets-global.website-files.com/5bbf9acbb5282f5328ad03fd/64df2e32ddd9f6557184e7d7_1200x630-thumb.jpg"
           width="500" height="250" alt="Sri Lanka Beach">
      <p>A regular paradise.</p>
      <p>We went for Sri Lanka in July and in this period, it's Arugam Bay season with plenty of right-handers
        mellow waves, perfect for those who prefer a chill ride over a gnarly one.</p>
      <p>But that’s not all; the island also boasts epic safaris where you can spot majestic elephants casually strolling by while you’re
        trying to catch the best sunset. It’s like a surf-and-safari combo deal where every day is an adventure
        and every night is a party.</p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <!-- Footer Section -->
  <footer>
    <p>&copy; 2024 Surftrip Around Indonesia & Sri Lanka. All rights reserved.</p>
  </footer>

  <!-- External JavaScript Files -->
  <%= javascript_include_tag 'scrolling-wrapper' %>
  <%= javascript_include_tag 'play-pause' %>

  <script>
  // Function to show the modal
  function showPresentation() {
    const modal = document.getElementById('presentation-modal');
    modal.style.display = 'flex'; // Change display to 'flex' to make it visible
  }

  // Optional: Function to close the modal when clicking outside of it
  window.onclick = function(event) {
    const modal = document.getElementById('presentation-modal');
    if (event.target === modal) {
      modal.style.display = 'none'; // Close the modal if the user clicks outside it
    }
  }
</script>

</body>
</html>
